-- India cbank chief says in talks with govt on monetary policy framework
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 06:43AM EDT
-- None



HYDERABAD, India, Oct 16 (Reuters) - Reserve Bank of India Governor Raghuram Rajan said on Thursday the central bank was in discussions with the government over the country's monetary policy framework, calling the relationship between the two sides "cordial."

Talks included setting objectives for the RBI, he said, while adding these talks did not threaten the independence of the central bank and were instead issues being worked out between the two sides.